tival \u2013 Farm fresh for 2018|website=phxveganfest.com}}</ref>\n\nThe Arizona Vegan Fest is scheduled for 22\u201323 December 2018, in Centennial Plaza, 9875 N 85th Ave, Peoria, AZ 85345. The organizers produce 2\u20133 free vegan festivals each year for Arizonans. AZ Vegan Fest seeks to concentrate Arizona's high quality vegan cuisine, products, ideas, and entertainment each year!<ref>{{cite web|url=http://azveganfest.com/|title=AZ Vegan Fest | website=azveganfest.com}}</ref>\n\n===== Scottsdale =====\nThe Arizona Veg Food Fest was held January 20\u201321, 2018, in the Scottsdale Civic Center Amphitheater in [[Scottsdale, Arizona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018215349/http://azvegfoodfest.com/|title=New York Veg Food Fest|author=|date=18 October 2014|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\nUnder different auspices and with slightly different organizing principles, a Scottsdale VegOut Vegan Festival was also held March 17\u201318, 2018.\n\n===== Sedona =====\nThe Sedona Vegfest was held January 20\u201321, 2018, in the Sedona Performing Arts Center.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://healthyworldsedona.com/sedona-vegfest-2017/|title=Sedona VegFest Celebration of Plant-Based Nutrition|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===== Tucson =====\nThe Third Annual VegFest Tucson is scheduled for Sunday, November 11, 2018, from 10am-5pmm at The Whistle Stop Depot, 127 W. 5th Street, in [[Tucson, Arizona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://foodinroot.com/veg/|title=Veg|website=FoodInRoot|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>  It is organized by It is organized by VegOut Tucson.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegoutevents.com/tucson-2018|title=2018 TUCSON \u2013 Vegout Events|author=|date=|website=VegOut! Events|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== California ====\n===== Berkeley =====\nThe annual Berkeley Vegan Earth Day is organized by Compassionate Living and longtime activist Hope Bohanec and was held on Sunday, April 22, 2018 \u2013 [[Earth Day]] \u2013 at the [[David Brower Center]] in [[Berkeley, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berkeleyveganearthday.com/|title=Berkeley Earth Day|website=Berkeleyveganearthday.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Encino =====\nVegFest L.A. (formerly WorldFest, a very popular event) was held on May 6, 2018, at 6004\u20136076 Woodley Avenue in [[Encino, California]], a neighborhood in the [[San Fernando Valley]] region of [[Los Angeles]].  \"World Fest was a solar-powered, day-long event filled with music, food, film and celebrities to raise public awareness of the veggie lifestyle. The first WorldFest was in 2000 at the same site, and was modeled after the San Diego FallFest held in 1999 in Ocean Beach.  This conference operated annually for thirteen years as WorldFest before being rebranded as VegFest.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfestevents.com/|title=World Fest \u2013 Music, Food, Film for the Veggie Lifestyle|website=Worldfestevents.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Irvine =====\nThe annual Vegan PlantFest was held on February 24, 2018, at Tanaka Farms in Irvine, California.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tanakafarms.com/events/2018/2/24/vegan-plant-fest-1000-to-300-no-reservation-needed|title=VEGAN PLANT FEST: 10:00 to 3:00 \u2013 no reservation needed|author=|date=|website=Tanaka Farms|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Long Beach =====\nThe second annual Long Beach Vegan Food & Music Festival was scheduled for July 8, 2017, and the third annual event is being scheduled for mid-July 2018, from 11 am to 7 pm, at Rainbow Lagoon Park, 400 Shoreline Village Drive, in [[Long Beach, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lbveganfest.com/home.html|title=Home|author=|date=|website=Long Beach Vegan Food and Music Festival|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Co-organizers Edward Yniguez and his wife, Kawani Brown, produce it annually.  Because the first year's event was free, reportedly between 8,500 and 10,000 people showed up throughout the day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lbpost.com/life/food/lbvf-recap/|title=Long Beach Vegan Fest Draws an Estimated 10,000 Attendees to Rainbow Lagoon Park \u2022 Long Beach Post|author=|date=|website=lbpost.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  But 2017 tickets cost $17 (general admission) to $45 (VIP tickets) each.\n\n===== Los Angeles =====\nThe Vegan Street Fair Los Angeles was held on March 25, 2018, at 11223 Chandler Boulevard in North Hollywood, California.\n\nThe Seed Food and Wine LA & Food Festival was held from May 23\u201327, 2018, in [[Los Angeles]], but some scheduling uncertainties remain.\n\nCalifornia Vegetarian Food Festival 2018 is scheduled for September 29, 2018, at Raleigh Studios Hollywood, 5300 Melrose Avenue, [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cavegfoodfest.com/|title=Home|author=|date=|website=www.cavegfoodfest.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> U.S. Veg Corp, organizer of this festival, is also organizing the NYC Vegetarian Food Festival 2018, to be held Saturday, May 19, 2018, beginning at 11:00 AM, at Metropolitan Pavilion, [[New York City]], where tickets are $30 \u2013 $75 each.\n\n===== Oakland =====\nOaklandVeg organizes an annual VegWeek in mid-May in [[Oakland, California]].  The 2018 event was held from May 12\u201320, ending with the Oakland VegFest, which was held for May 20, 2018, from 11 am to 5 pm, at the Lake Merritt Amphitheater.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150219143242/http://oaklandveg.com/overview/|title=Overview \u2013 Oakland Veg \u2013 California|author=|date=19 February 2015|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oaklandvegfest.com/|title=Oakland VegFest|website=oaklandvegfest.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/1896232510620160/|title=2017 Oakland VegFest|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Pasadena =====\nThe Eat Drink Vegan (Formerly Known as Vegan Beer & Food Festival) was held on May 26, 2018, on [[Memorial Day]] Weekend, in [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|The Rose Bowl]] in [[Pasadena]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eatdrinkvegan.com/|title=Eat Drink Vegan|author=|date=|website=Eat Drink Vegan|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The Festival features unlimited pours of the region's best craft beer, wine, ciders, kombucha, cold brew, craft sodas, and tea tastings at the Rose Bowl and Brookside Golf Course... and involves 100+ exhibitors who are restaurants, food carts, trucks, and other vendors. The Green Saturday Vegan Marketplace showcases vendors selling products from clothing to skin care.\n\n===== Sacramento =====\nThe SacTown VegFest, was held January 27, 2018, in the Sacramento High School, 2315 34th Street.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sactownvegfest.org/|title=SacTown VegFest|website=SacTown VegFest}}</ref>  The 2019 event will be scheduled for a comparable date.\n\n===== San Diego =====\nThe Vegan Street Fair San Diego Nights was held Saturday, May 12, 2018, at Anthem Vegan in San Diego.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kpbs.org/events/2018/may/12/vegan-street-fair-san-diego/?et=91182|title=Vegan Street Fair San Diego|author=|date=|website=KPBS Public Media|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  For hygienic and permit reasons, dogs were not allowed at the food event.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/vegan-street-fair-vegas-nights-2018/171428313499043/|title=Vegan Street Fair Vegas Nights 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== San Jose =====\nThe South Bay VegFair is scheduled for June 16, 2018, at the Santa Clara County Fairgrounds in [[San Jose, California]].<ref>https://www.summerveg.com/</ref>\n\n===== San Luis Obispo =====\nThe Central Coast Veg Fest was held in San Luis Obispo, CA on February 17, 2018, at San Luis Obispo Veteran's Hall at 801 Grand Avenue.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ccveg.org/|title=Central Coast VegFest February 23rd, 2019 \u2013 Vegan Festival in SLO, CA|author=|date=|website=Central Coast Veg & VegFest|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Yucaipa =====\nTen miles east of [[San Bernardino]], at [[Crafton Hills College]], [[Yucaipa]], there is the herbivorefestival.<ref>{{cite web|title=herbivore festival|url=http://www.herbivorefestival.com|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nIt has been held In early October in previous years, but most recently it was held on May 6, 2018.  It is free to the general public, run entirely by volunteers, and features scores of vegan exhibitors of various kinds.<ref>{{cite web|title=herbivore festival|url=http://herbivorefestival.com/index.html|accessdate=21 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== Colorado ====\n===== Broomfield =====\nVegFest Colorado is scheduled for July 28\u201329, 2018, for 1stBank Center, 11450 Broomfield Lane, in [[Broomfield, Colorado]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegfestcolorado.org/home.html|title=VegFest Colorado \u2013 VegFest, Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=VegFest Colorado|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The 2017 event largely featured vegan food leaders (vegan chefs, vegan cookbook authors, vegan food bloggers) and reported attracted about 4000 attendees each day.\n\n===== Denver =====\nVegFest Colorado is run 100% by volunteers and open to the public.<ref>{{cite web|title=Veg Fest Colorado|url=http://www.vegfestcolorado.org|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== Connecticut ====\n===== Hamden =====\nThe Annual Compassionfest is held outdoors on a mid-July Saturday each summer, from 10 am to 5 pm, at the Whitneyville Cultural Commons, 1253 Whitney Avenue in [[Hamden, Connecticut]].  Speakers and exhibitors include local vegan luminaries, including art historian and vegan author [[Mark Braunstein]].\n\nThe 4th Annual Compassionfest was held on Saturday, July 21, 2018, from 10 am to 5 pm, 1253 Whitney Avenue in [[Hamden, Connecticut]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.compassionfest.net/|title=Compassionfest \u2013 It's about community. It's about equality. It's about kindness. Compassion.|author=|date=|website=www.compassionfest.net|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe 5th Annual Compassionfest is scheduled for July 20, 2019, at the same location.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.meetup.com/Boston-Vegetarian-Meetup/events/263150356/|title=5th Annual CompassionFest \u2013 Hamden, CT|website=Meetup|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.compassionfest.net/|title=Compassionfest &#124; It's about community. It's about equality. It's about kindness. Compassion.|website=www.compassionfest.net|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Delaware ====\n===== Rehoboth Beach =====\nThe Rehoboth VegFest was held on Saturday, June 9, 2018, at the Epworth United Methodist Church on Holland Glade Road in [[Rehoboth Beach, Delaware]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegrehoboth.org/|title=VegRehoboth|author=|date=|website=vegrehoboth.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The organizer, VegRehoboth, is a non-profit social and outreach organization that promotes healthy, sustainable, and compassionate living!  They hold at least two public events each month, and usually more than ten public vegan-friendly events.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegrehoboth.org/|title=VegRehoboth|author=|date=|website=VegRehoboth|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The event features compassionate vegan speakers, compassionate causes, musical performances, craft and product vendors, vegan food vendors, other topical exhibitors, and workshops and demos.  Attendance is free and open to the general public.\n\n==== Florida ====\n===== Bonita Springs =====\nThe SWFL (Southwest Florida) Veg Fest was held on January 28, 2018, at Riverside Park in Bonita Springs, FL.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swflvegfest.org/|title=SWFL Veg Fest \u2013 For people, animals & the planet|website=Swflvegfest.org|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Gainesville =====\nThe Gainesville VegFest was held for February 17, 2018, in Depot Park, 200 Southeast Depot Avenue, in [[Gainesville, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gainesvillevegfest.com/|title=Home \u2013 Gainesville Veg Fest|website=Gainesville Veg Fest}}</ref>  The 2019 date will be in February.\n\n===== Jacksonville =====\nThe Northeast Florida VegFest was held on March 3, 2018, in Riverside Park in [[Jacksonville, Florida]].  The sponsor is Girls Gone Green (GGG).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfvegfest.org/|title=Northeast Florida Veg Fest|website=Northeast Florida Veg Fest}}</ref>\n\n===== Orlando =====\nThe 13th Annual Central Florida Earth Day, organized by Vegetarians of Central Florida, was held on [[Earth Day]] \u2013 Sunday, April 22, 2018 \u2013 in [[Lake Eola Park]], 512 East Washington Street, in [[Orlando, Florida]].  Earth Day is the largest and longest-running Earth Day festival in Central Florida!<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cfearthday.org/|title=Central Florida Earth Day|website=Central Florida Earth Day}}</ref>  It is also coordinated with Central Florida's local March for Science, beginning at 10 am.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/134957923682840|title=March For Science: Orlando, Fla.|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Solutionary Peace Walk & Festival is scheduled to be presented by Solutionary Events around Lake Eola Park (512 E. Washington Street) in [[Orlando, Florida]] and to occur in June 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.solutionaryevents.com/|title=solutionaryevents|author=|date=|website=solutionaryevents|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  \"Solutionary Events is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization with a mission to create healthy, compassionate, and environmentally regenerative communities through leading socially responsible vegan events all throughout the state of Florida and beyond. Solutionary Events is operated entirely by dedicated volunteers. The team coordinates festivals, race/walks, monthly film screenings, beach/park cleanups, workshops, school programs, meetups, and other educational events.'\n\n===== Sarasota =====\nThe Sarasota Veg Fest was held on May 5, 2018, from 10 am to 5 pm, at the Sarasota Fairgrounds, 10:00 am \u2013 5:00 pm, 3000 Ringling Blvd, in [[Sarasota, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.meetup.com/vegsarasota/|title=VegSarasota Vegetarian & Vegan Meetup Group (Sarasota, FL)|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegsarasota.com/|title=VegSarasota \u2013 Your vegan guide to Sarasota, Bradenton, Venice and the Keys.|website=VegSarasota}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/groups/81324524183/|title=Log into Facebook \u2013 Facebook|website=Facebook}}</ref><ref>http://www.solutionaryfestival.org/blog/sarasota-veg-fest/</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sarasotavegfest.org/|title=Sarasota Veg Fest \u2013 Sarasota's Grand Celebration of Healthy, Compassionate, and Eco-Friendly Living|author=|date=|website=sarasotavegfest.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Tallahassee =====\nThe first North Florida VegFest occurred in 2015, with over 2,500 attendees. The annual event is organized by the Tallahassee Vegetarian Community (TalVeg). The second annual event occurred on March 20, 2016, at Cascades Park, Tallahassee.<ref>{{cite web|title=North Florida VegFest|url=http://www.northfloridavegfest.com|accessdate=15 March 2016}}</ref>  The fourth annual North Florida VegFest was held March 17, 2018, in Cascades Park in \n[[Tallahassee, Florida]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.northfloridavegfest.com/|title=North Florida VegFest|website=Northfloridavegfest.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== Georgia ====\n===== Metro Atlanta =====\nAtlanta Veg Fest is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization whose mission is to support their local community and to promote the recognized benefits of a plant-based vegan lifestyle, often motivated by compassion for animals, humans, and the ecosystem.  The 8th annual Atlanta Veg Fest will be held on November 9, 2019, at [[Infinite Energy Center]] in [[Duluth, Georgia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://atlantavegfest.com/|title=Atlanta Veg Fest|website=atlantavegfest.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==== Illinois ====\n===== Chicago =====\nVeggie Fest in [[Lisle, Illinois]] (a Chicago suburb) is one of the largest vegetarian food and lifestyle festivals in [[North America]] and has been held annually since 2005, celebrating its 10th anniversary in 2015. Over 800 volunteers have helped in the festival. Over 30,000 people attended in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Veggie Fest Chicago|url=http://www.veggiefestchicago.com/index.php|accessdate=29 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nChicago \u2013 Vegandale Food Drink Festival (formerly Chicago Vegan Food and Drink Fest) is held annually in Grant Park, Butler Field, 100 South Lake Shore Drive, in [[Chicago]].<ref>https://www.vegandrinkfest.com/chicago/</ref> Chicago Vegan Food and Drink Fest was held 2016\u20132018 before changing names.\n\nCelebrate Vegan Fest: Chicago is planned for 2020; this was previously Chicago Veganmania, which outgrew its previous location at the Chicago Armory.<ref>https://www.celebratevegan.org/faqs</ref>  Chicago Veganmania started in 2008 and ran through 2018.<ref>https://www.blogger.com/profile/10488182632304575272</ref>\n\n==== Indiana ====\n===== Indianapolis =====\nThe Indy VegFest, an all vegan event, started on Saturday, March 31, 2018, from 12 noon to 6 pm, at the Biltwell Event Center in [[Indianapolis, Indiana]].  In 2020 it will be held at the Bankers Life Fieldhouse.  The event appears to be set for either the last Saturday or Sunday of March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indyvegfest.com/|title=Indy VegFest \u2013 Indianapolis|author=|date=|website=indyvegfest.com}}</ref>\n\n===== Notre Dame =====\nThe Michiana VegFest was held March 25, 2018, in Corbett Family Hall and in the Downes Ballroom of the [[University of Notre Dame]].  It featured speakers, vegan culinary demonstrations, and protected fun for children.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://veganmichiana.com/event/michiana-vegfest-2018/|title=Michiana VegFest 2018|author=|date=|website=veganmichiana.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://michianavegfest.org/|title=Michiana Veg Fest \u2013 April 14, 2019 at the Century Center in South Bend|website=Michiana Veg Fest|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>  In 2019 the Michiana VegFest moved to April 14 at the Century Center in South Bend,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sustainabilitystudies.nd.edu/news-events/events/2019/04/14/michiana-veg-fest/|title=Michiana Veg Fest|accessdate=22 December 2019}}</ref> and the 2020 event is also planned for April at the Century Center.  The festival is plant-based (vegan).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://michianavegfest.org/|title=Michiana Veg Fest|accessdate=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Iowa ====\n===== Des Moines =====\nThe Des Moines VeganFest was hosted by VegLife Des Moines and held in the Valley Community Center at 4444 Fuller Road in [[Des Moines, Iowa]], from 11 am to 5 pm on Saturday, March 24, 2018, and featured speakers and 42 vendors or tablers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://veglifedesmoines.org/veganfest-2018/vendors/|title=Vendors|author=|date=1 November 2017|website=veglifedesmoines.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://veglifedesmoines.org/veganfest-2018/volunteer/|title=Volunteer|author=|date=1 November 2017|website=veglifedesmoines.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The fest moved to April 27 in 2019, at The Atrium at Capital Square & Cowles Commons\n(400 Locust Street) in Des Moines.  Note $5 admission charge (17 and under free).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://veglifedesmoines.org/veganfest|title=VeganFest 2019|accessdate=22 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Louisiana ====\n===== New Orleans =====\nNOLA VeggieFest is organized by the Humane Society of Louisiana, and had been scheduled for May 13 (11am-6pm) to 14 (12 noon to 6 pm), 2018, at The Kingsley House, 1600 Constance Street, in New Orleans, Louisiana.  The event is free to the general public.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nolaveggiefest.com/|title=About the NOLA Veggie Fest|website=NOLA Veggie Fest}}</ref>  However, the organizers decided to not hold the 2018 event and to reorganize the event and offer it next in Spring 2019.\n\n==== Maine ====\n===== Portland =====\nThe Maine Animal Coalition's [[Maine VegFest]] was held on Saturday, June 2, 2018, at the East End School, 195 North Street, in [[Portland, Maine]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pressherald.com/2016/05/25/vegetarian-kitchen-surge-in-food-festivals-for-plant-eaters-reflects-lifestyles-growth/|title=Surge in food festivals for plant eaters reflects lifestyle\u2019s growth|last=Kamila|first=Avery Yale|date=2016-05-25|website=Portland Press Herald|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.maineanimalcoalition.org/vegetarian-food-festival|title=Veg Fest|author=|date=|website=maineanimalcoalition.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> The 15th Annual Maine VegFest will be held Sunday, November 3, 2019 11 am to 3 pm Italian Heritage Center, 40 Westland Avenue, Portland, Maine 04102. Admission and parking are free to all, and special speakers include engineer and self-taught vegan chef and cookbook author, Colin McCollough, who had become very well known for his earlier work in biodiesel; Christen Mailler of Vegan Publishers; and 37-year medical doctor Dr. Timothy R. Howe, whose plant-based vegan medical practice is 25 years old.<ref>[https://www.maineanimalcoalition.org/vegetarian-food-festival Home page for Annual Maine VegFest]</ref><ref>[https://www.healthgrades.com/physician/dr-timothy-howe-35by4]</ref><ref>[https://www.plantbaseddoctors.org/timothy-howe Plant-Based Medical Doctors profile for Timothy R. Howe, MD]</ref>\n\n==== Maryland ====\n===== Baltimore =====\nThe annual Baltimore Veg Fest, \"an annual celebration of healthy, sustainable, and compassionate eating\", is scheduled for sometime in mid-May at the Erickson Field UMBC Campus in [[Baltimore]] and is organized by and supported by The Humane League.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thehumaneleague.org/|title=Farm animal protection nonprofit|author=|date=|website=thehumaneleague.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The 7th Annual Baltimore VegFest was held in April 2017, and the next event will be in 2019 because complications preventing holding the Spring 2018 event.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/category/Nonprofit-Organization/The-Annual-Baltimore-VegFest-263956273645903/|title=The Annual Baltimore VegFest|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe 5th Annual Baltimore Vegan SoulFest will be held on Saturday, August 25, 2018, from 12:00 noon through 7:00PM, at Clifton Park, 2801 Harford Road, in [[Baltimore]], and admission is free and open to the general public.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegansoulfest.com/|title=Vegan SoulFest|author=|date=|website=Vegan SoulFest|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Coordinators are Naijha Wright and Brenda Sanders.\n\n==== Massachusetts ====\n=====Boston=====\nThe [[Boston Vegetarian Society#Boston Vegetarian Food Festival (BVFF)|Boston Vegetarian Food Festival (BVFF)]] is held annually in the autumn, at the [[Reggie Lewis Track and Athletic Center]] in [[Mission Hill, Boston]] between mid-October and early November.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tech.mit.edu/V119/N40/Veggie40.40a.html |title=THE ESSENTIAL VEGETARIAN: Cheese: The vegetarian's friend in Europe \u2013 The Tech |work=Tech.mit.edu |date=1999-09-10 |accessdate=2012-07-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tech.mit.edu/V120/N47/veggie47.47a.html |title=FOOD REVIEW: The Essential Vegetarian \u2013 The Tech |work=Tech.mit.edu |date=2000-10-03 |accessdate=2012-07-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boston.com/lifestyle/food/articles/2010/10/30/boston_vegetarian_food_festival_at_reggie_lewis_athletic_center/ |title=Boston Vegetarian Food Festival at Reggie Lewis Athletic Center \u2013 The Boston Globe |work=Boston.com |date=2010-10-30 |accessdate=2012-07-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://digboston.com/taste/2010/10/boston-vegetarian-food-fest-dont-drink-the-kombucha/ |title=BOSTON VEGETARIAN FOOD FEST: Don't drink the Kombucha |publisher=DigBoston |date=2010-10-26 |accessdate=2012-07-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111116011418/http://digboston.com/taste/2010/10/boston-vegetarian-food-fest-dont-drink-the-kombucha/ |archive-date=2011-11-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Weiss |first=Rachel |url=http://articles.boston.com/2011-10-27/yourtown/30328737_1_vegetarian-cuisine-roxbury-vegan |title=Vegetarian Food Festival in Roxbury growing in popularity |work=Articles.boston.com |date=2011-10-27 |accessdate=2012-07-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111030175829/http://articles.boston.com/2011-10-27/yourtown/30328737_1_vegetarian-cuisine-roxbury-vegan |archive-date=2011-10-30 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Begun first in May 1996, it may be the oldest vegetarian food festival in the United States, having been copied from the Toronto Vegetarian Food Fair.  The 2019 two-day event was held on Saturday-Sunday, 19\u201320 October 2019.<ref>[http://www.BostonVeg.org/foodfest/ Landing page for annual Boston Vegetarian Food Festival]</ref>\n\n=====Northampton=====\nThe annual Valley Vegfest: a celebration of compassionate living, was organized by ValleyVeg and held on April 7, 2018, at the J.F.K. Middle School in [[Northampton, Massachusetts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valleyveg.org/vegfest/|title=Valley Vegfest \u2013 a celebration of compassionate living|website=Valleyveg.org|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n=====Worcester=====\nThe New England VegFest (formerly Worcester VegFest) is a free festival that brings the local community together to celebrate vegetarianism at the [[DCU Center]] at 50 Foster Street in downtown [[Worcester, Massachusetts]].  The 2018 event was held on Sunday, April 29, 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newenglandvegfest.com/|title=New England VegFest|website=newenglandvegfest.com}}</ref> and the 2019 event is on Sunday, April 28, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newenglandvegfest.com/|title=New England VegFest|website=newenglandvegfest.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://member.vegfest.org/|title=Become a member of VegFest today!|website=VegFest.org|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/newenglandvegfest/|title=New England VegFest|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Michigan ====\n===== Detroit =====\nV313, Detroit's Vegan Celebration, was held from 3:00 PM through 9:00 PM on March 3, 2018, in Shed 5 of the Eastern Market at 2930 Russell Street @Alfred Stin in [[Detroit, Michigan]].  It was organized and sponsored by the Plant-Based Nutrition Support Group (PBNSG), VegMichigan, and VegSpeedDate, and featured speakers such as Dr. [[Caldwell Esselstyn]] of [[Cleveland Clinic]], Dr. Joel Kahn, Dr. Milton Mills of [[Physicians Committee for Responsible Medicine]], and Dr. Kerrie Saunders (a.k.a. Dr. Food) and \"plant-powered musicians\" such as 'Rosie and the Fellas' and 'Once United'.  The $15 per person tickets were sold online and at the door.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hourdetroit.com/Web-Exclusives/One-Day-Vegan-Festival-Comes-to-Detroits-Eastern-Market/|title=One-Day Vegan Festival Comes to Detroit's Eastern Market|author=|date=|website=www.hourdetroit.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pbnsg.org/event-calendar/2018/3/8/v313-detroits-premier-vegan-celebration|title=V313: Detroit's Premier Vegan Celebration|author=|date=|website=PBNSG|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metrotimes.com/table-and-bar/archives/2018/02/15/v313-a-one-day-vegan-festival-is-planned-for-detroits-eastern-market|title='V313,' a one-day vegan festival, is planned for Detroit's Eastern Market|first=Lee|last=DeVito|website=Detroit Metro Times|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fox2detroit.com/good-day/cooking-school-sponsored-by-andiamo/v313-vegan-celebration-at-eastern-market-march-8|title=V313 vegan celebration at Eastern Market March 8|last=FOX|date=|website=WJBK|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bodymindspiritguide.com/2018/02/17/march-8th-eastern-market-host-v313-detroits-premier-vegan-celebration/|title=March 8th Eastern Market to Host V313: Detroit's Premier Vegan Celebration|author=|date=17 February 2018|website=bodymindspiritguide.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eventbrite.com/e/42281963491?aff=efbneb|title=V313: Detroit's Premier Vegan Celebration|author=|date=|website=Eventbrite|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://migreenteam.com/V313/|title=V313: Detroit's Premier Vegan Celebration|author=|date=|website=migreenteam.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  V313 was an alcohol-free event.<ref>[htt[://www.V313.info.]</ref>\n\n===== Grand Rapids =====\nGrand Rapids' festival includes popular speakers and bountiful food offerings, including El Cardenal Vegan Tamales.  It is held the second Sunday in September.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://grvegfest.com|title=Grand Rapids Veg Fest|website=Grand Rapids Veg Fest}}</ref>  The 4th Annual Grand Rapids VegFest was held in the DeltaPlex Arena, 2500 Turner Avenue, NW, Grand Rapids, on Sunday, October 7, 2019, from 10:30 am to 5 pm, with free admission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://grvegfest.com/home/who-are-we-2/|title=What is GR VegFest?|author=|date=|website=Grand Rapids Veg Fest|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The Grand Rapids VegFest manager is Kim Kyunghee Enochs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/soulditto|title=Kim Kyunghee Enochs|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/GRvegfest/|title=Grand Rapids Veg Fest|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Novi =====\nThe 2018 Michigan VegFest was held on Sunday, April 29, 2018, at [[Suburban Collection Showplace]] in Novi.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/VegMichiganFan/|title=VegMichigan|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>  American retired professional [[basketball]] player, actor, [[talk show host]], and vegan activist [[John Salley]] spoke at VegMichigan's Michigan Vegfest from 2009\u20132012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Veg Fest Michigan|url=http://vegmichigan.org/activities/vegfest/|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n==== Minnesota ====\n===== Minneapolis-St. Paul =====\nTwin Cities Veg Fest, organized annually by [[Compassionate Action for Animals]], presents [[vegan]] food and product vendors, food preparation demonstrations, vegan educational speakers, vegan cultural music, art, and informational exhibitors, such as farm sanctuaries, animal advocacy groups, and dietitians, nutritionists, and health educators.  CAA's first event indoors in 2012 reported more than 1,200 attendees.  Annual attendance at the indoor September events grew so that, in 2017, the event was moved outside to accommodate anticipated crowd size. It now is considered to be the largest vegan festival in the [[US Midwest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/tcvegfest|title=Twin Cites Veg Fest|website=Facebook.com|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref> The 2019 festival, scheduled for Harriet Island Park<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harriet_Island_Pavilion/|title=Harriet Island Pavilion|website=en.wikipedia.org|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>{{Circular reference|date=March 2019}}, is expected to draw over 10,000 attendees.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.exploreveg.org/programs/twin-cities-veg-fest/|title=Twin Cites Veg Fest|website=exploreveg.org|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref>\n\n==== Missouri ====\n===== Kansas City =====\nVegFest Kansas City's inaugural event was on June 24, 2017 at the City Market Park. It featured plant-based companies, speakers, and cooking demonstrations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/1576620075981919/|title=VegFest Kansas City 2017|website=Facebook.com|access-date=2017-12-09}}</ref>  The annual 2018 VegFest Kansas City was organized by Voice for Animals and held June 2018 in The City Market Park, 300 Main Street, in [[Kansas City, Missouri]].<ref>http://americanvegan.org/vegfestkc.com</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vegfestkc.com/exhibitors/|title=\u7535\u5de5\u8bba\u575b--\u60a8\u7684\u8bbf\u95ee\u51fa\u9519\u4e86 \u2013 \u9001\u4f53\u9a8c\u91d1\u5b98\u7f51|author=|date=|website=www.vegfestkc.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Nevada ====\n===== Las Vegas =====\nThe first Vegas VegFest took place on April 9 of 2016. It was 100% volunteer organized and featured local vegan options,  speakers, cooking demonstrations, live music, kids' activities, and animal-oriented nonprofits.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegas VegFest |url=http://www.vegasvegfest.com|accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe Vegan Street Fair Vegas Nights occurred on March 5, 2018, in [[Las Vegas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.veganstreetfair.com/|title=Vegan Street Fair \u2013 Vegan \u2013 Los Angeles -|website=Vegan Street Fair \u2013 Vegan \u2013 Los Angeles -}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\"/>  The commercial organizers coordinate similar events around the United States, with intervals of several months between each event.\n\n==== New Hampshire ====\n===== Lebanon =====\nOn Saturday, July 13, 2019, the annual Mountain Veg Fest was held outdoors in Colburn Park, 51 North Park Street, Lebanon, NH, USA.<ref>[\nhttps://www.meetup.com/vegan-430/events/262566241 Meetup.com event page for Mountain Veg Fest 2019, Saturday, July 13, 2019]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/mountain-veg-fest/mountain-veg-fest-2019/2430723507213817/|title=Mountain Veg Fest 2019!|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>  Speakers included Captain [[Paul Watson]] of [[Sea Shepherd]].  Admission was free to the public park, and donations were announced as funding improved equipment for outdoor presentations to the crowds.\n\n===== Manchester =====\nThe Sixth Annual New Hampshire VegFest was held Saturday, April 14, 2018, from 9:00am to 3:00pm, at [[Manchester Community College (New Hampshire)|Manchester Community College]] in [[Manchester, New Hampshire]].  The event is run entirely by volunteers and offers free admission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nhvegfest.com/|title=Home|website=nhvegfest}}</ref>\n\n==== New Jersey ====\n===== Atlantic City =====\nThe Atlantic City Vegan Food Festival, organized by New Jersey VegFest<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/NewJerseyVegFest/ New Jersey VegFest Facebook page]</ref>, was held on July 14, 2018, from 10am \u2013 5pm at Showboat Atlantic City Hotel in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://njvegfest.com/|title=New Jersey VegFest|author=|date=|website=New Jersey VegFest|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and the following year for a full summer weekend from Friday, July 12, 2019, through Sunday, July 14, 2019, also at Showboat Atlantic City Hotel on the boardwalk in [[Atlantic City, New Jersey]].<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/events/showboat-hotel-atlantic-city/atlantic-city-vegan-food-festival-2019-july-12-14/1970814156546583/ Atlantic City Vegan Food Festival 2019: July 12-14. Hosted by New Jersey VegFest.  Facebook.]</ref>\n\n===== Edison =====\nThe 3rd Annual Tri-State Veg Fest Expois scheduled for June 16, 2018, from 12 noon to 6 pm, at The New Jersey Convention and Exposition Center, 97 Sunfield Avenue, in [[Edison, New Jersey]].  Tickets are $20 per person, with VIP tickets sold at $60 each.<ref name=\"vegfestexpos.com\">{{cite web|url=https://vegfestexpos.com/|title=South Florida Vegfest|author=|date=|website=VegFest Expos|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Morristown =====\nThe Vegan PopUp Shop is scheduled for Sunday, February 25, from 10 am to 6 pm, at the Laundromat Bar in [[Morristown, New Jersey]].<ref name=\"vegfestexpos.com\"/>\n\n===== Secaucus =====\nThe New Jersey VegFest 2018 is scheduled for Saturday and Sunday, October 6\u20137, 2018, from 10 am to 5 pm, at Meadowlands Expo Center in [[Secaucus, New Jersey]].<ref name=\"vegfestexpos.com\"/>\n\n==== New Mexico ====\n===== Albuquerque =====\nThe first three Red and Green VegFest Albuquerque were held in 2016, 2017, and 2018 in the [[Albuquerque Convention Center]] in \n[[Albuquerque, New Mexico]], and last year on March 10, 2018.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://redandgreenvegfestabq.wordpress.com/|title=Red & Green VegFest Albuquerque|website=Red & Green VegFest Albuquerque}}</ref>  The fourth (2019) New Mexico Vegan and Red & Green VegFest Albuquerque will be held again at 9 am on August 10, 2019, in the same location as in previous years.<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n\n==== New York ====\n===== Albany =====\nAlbany VegFest is organized by Capital Region Vegan Network (CRVN).  The 12th Albany VegFest will take place on Sunday, October 4, 2020 at the Albany Capital Center.<ref>https://capregionvegans.org/albany-vegfest/</ref>\nCRVN also organizes VEG OUT, a vegan street fair, held in June in downtown Troy, NY.<ref>https://capregionvegans.org/veg-out/</ref>\n\n===== Brooklyn =====\nThe Seed Experience<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yelp.com/biz/the-seed-experience-brooklyn-2|title=The Seed Experience \u2013 CLOSED \u2013 Greenpoint \u2013 Brooklyn, NY|website=Yelp}}</ref> is scheduled for April 2018, in the Brooklyn Expo Center at 72 Noble Street<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nycgo.com/venues/brooklyn-expo-center|title=Brooklyn Expo Center|website=NYCgo.com}}</ref> in the [[Brooklyn]] borough of [[New York, New York]].\n\n===== New York City =====\nThe New York Vegetarian Vision Festival, which operated for several years during the late 1990s, was organized by NYC-based Vegetarian Vision, a nonprofit organization composed mostly of professional vegetarians from India who were largely devout [[Jain]]s or [[Hindus]].  They copied their event from the [[Boston Vegetarian Society#Boston Vegetarian Food Festival (BVFF)|Boston Vegetarian Food Festival (BVFF)]], which had copied their event from the Toronto Vegetarian Food Fair.\n\nThe current NYC Vegetarian Food Festival is organized by U.S. Veg Corp., a nonprofit founded by Sarah Gross Feoli and Nira Paliwoda.<ref>{{cite web|title=NYC Vegetarian Food Festival|url=http://nycvegfoodfest.com/|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\nLast year's two-day NYC Vegetarian Food Festival was held on May 19\u201320, 2018, at The Metropolitan Pavilion, 125 West 18th Street, in [[New York City]].  General admission is $30 each plus a $3.72 Exhibit Fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124051704/http://www.nycvegfoodfest.com/Welcome.html|title=COMING MARCH 2011|author=|date=24 November 2010|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe 11th annual Veggie Pride Parade was held on April 8, 2018, beginning in Greenwich Village/Union Square in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.veggieprideparade.org/|title=Veggie Pride Parade, New York City|website=Veggieprideparade.org|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://allevents.in/events/11th-annual-veggie-pride-parade-nyc/2265336573679443|title=11th Annual Veggie Pride Parade NYC|website=Allevents.in|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>  This is the first annual Veggie Pride Parade which was not organized by Pamela Rice and VivaVegie, which had started and organized the event for ten years.  This year's event was organized by [[The Humane League]].\n\nThe annual Vegan Street Fair New York Nights was held on Saturday, June 9, 2018, at West 8th Street between 5th & 6th, New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.veganstreetfair.com/|title=Vegan Street Fair \u2013 Vegan \u2013 Los Angeles -|author=|date=|website=Vegan Street Fair \u2013 Vegan \u2013 Los Angeles -|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Vegan Street Fair Events is a private vegetarian-value company which profitably organizes such events in various locations around the United States.  \"VSF LA and VSF NY are our two FREE annual mainstay events.\"  \"The VSF Nights Tour has rotating cities every year while VSF LA Nights is an annual mainstay event.\"  VSF Nights are organized commercially in four American cities: [[North Hollywood]], New York, [[Seattle]], and [[Las Vegas]].  VSF began in 2015, and \"VSF and VSF Nights are expected to be in 6 US cities by 2018.\"  The additional two American cities are yet to be named.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n\n===== Buffalo =====\n\nWNY VegFest is organized by WNY Vegans. It is typically held the first Sunday in August, is free to attend, is organized by volunteers, and includes a Tofurky Trot.<ref name=\"wnyvegfest1\"/>\n\n==== North Carolina ====\n===== Asheville =====\n\nThe Asheville Vegan Fest is scheduled for June 8\u201310, 2018, in Pack Square Park at 80 Court Square Park in downtown [[Asheville, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://veganfest.bwar.org/|title=VeganFest|author=|date=|website=bwar.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  All three days of events are free to the public, and Sunday's Asheville VeganFest Outdoor Festival runs from 11am to 6pm.\n\n===== Charlotte =====\nThe 7th Annual Charlotte VegFest for 2018 is scheduled for Freedom Hall at the Park Expo and Conference Center, 800 Briar Creek Road, in [[Charlotte, North Carolina]] for Saturday, October 13, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/CharlotteVegFest/|title=Charlotte Vegfest|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://veganclt.com/charlotte-vegfest/about/|title=When is Charlotte VegFest?|author=|date=|website=veganclt.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The 6th Annual Charlotte VegFest, the region's largest vegan festival, was held in April 2017 at the Park Expo, from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m.  Speakers included Will Tucker, professional vegan bodybuilder, and The Good Food Institute's Emily Byrd.  More than 100 exhibitors were featured, as were VegSpeedDating and vegan culinary demonstrations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://clture.org/charlotte-veg-fest/|title=Why you should check out Charlotte VegFest|author=|date=27 April 2017|website=clture.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Wilmington =====\nWilmington Vegan's First Wilmington Vegfest was held on Saturday, April 14, 2018, at the Coastline Conference Center, 501 Nutt Street, in [[Wilmington, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wilmingtonvegan.com/wilmington-vegfest/|title=Wilmington VegFest|website=Wilmington Vegan}}</ref><ref name=\"facebook.com\">{{cite web|url=https://facebook.com/ncvegfests|title=Wilmington Vegfest|website=Facebook.com}}</ref>  Reportedly, this nonprofit event is being organized by the Executive Director from Triangle VegFest, which is sponsored annually by Triangle Vegetarian Society.\n\n==== Ohio ====\n===== Cleveland =====\nThe 2018 Cleveland VegFest was held for May 5, 2018, from 11:00 AM \u2013 7:00 PM, at the [[Huntington Convention Center of Cleveland]] at 300 Lakeside Ave East.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clevelandvegansociety.org/|title=Welcome|website=The Cleveland Vegan Society}}</ref>  Admission was free, but a $5 donation was requested at the door.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clevelandvegansociety.org/vegfest-home|title=VegFest Home|author=|date=|website=The Cleveland Vegan Society|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The 2019 Cleveland VegFest is scheduled for May 18, 2019, again from 11:00 AM \u2013 7:00 PM, at the [[Huntington Convention Center of Cleveland]], and with the same free admission but $5 donation requested.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https