sociation. The festival organisers stipulate only vegan products be offered at the event by vendors. Admission is free to attendees.\n\n=== Indonesia ===\nThe first Bali Vegan Festival started in 2015 at Down To Earth (Ubud).<ref>{{cite web|title=Bali Vegan Festival|url=http://www.baliveganfestival.com/|accessdate=26 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Japan ===\nThe Vegetarian Festival in Tokyo started in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tokyo Vegefood Fiesta|url=http://tokyo-vegefest.com/english/|website=Tokyo-vegefest.com|accessdate=21 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151015041509/http://tokyo-vegefest.com/english/|archive-date=15 October 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Philippines ===\nThe Philippines had its first 3-leg vegan festival \u2013 VegFest Pilipinas \u2013 in November and December 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=VegFest Pilipinas|url=http://vegfestpilipinas.com/|website=Vegfestpilipinas.com|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe 2017 event was two 2-day VegFest Pilipinas events at two different locations: from 18\u201319 November 2017 in Eastwood City, with 'Hair,' Pilita in concert, and VegFest Pilipinas in Chinatown the following weekend, 25\u201326 November 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegfestpilipinas.strikingly.com/|title=VegFest Pilipinas on Strikingly|author=|date=|website=VegFest Pilipinas|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.astigvegan.com/vegfest-pilipinas-2017/|title=Enriquez RG. VegFest Pilipinas 2017, A Recap of what happened. December 8, 2017|author=|date=|website=astigvegan.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The 2018 event again will be two 2-day VegFest Pilipinas events at two different locations: held one weekend from 8 am to 10 pm, 18\u201319 November 2018, at the BGC Arts Center in the Eastwood Central Plaza Shopping Mall, [[Quezon City]], [[Metro Manila]], [[Philippines]]; then again, the following weekend, 25\u201326 November 2017, in Lucky Chinatown, Binondo, [[Metro Manila]], [[Philippines]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/category/Community/VegFestPilipinas/posts/|title=VegFest Pilipinas|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Singapore ===\n{{see also|EarthFest (SG)}}\nThe [[EarthFest (SG)|EarthFest Singapore]] had its debut in September 2015 and was sponsored by Singapore's [[Vegetarian Society (Singapore)|Vegetarian Society]] and others.\n\n=== Thailand ===\nThe Vegetarian Festival in Bangkok takes place each fall.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Vegetarian Festival|url=http://www.bangkok.com/whats-on-events/vegetarian-festival.htm|website=Bangkok.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{see also|Nine Emperor Gods Festival#Celebration in Thailand}}\nThis vegetarian festival is a nine-day period in October that celebrates the abstinence from meat during the ninth lunar month of the Chinese calendar.\n\n=== Vietnam ===\nThe Vegan Festival in Ho Chi Minh City takes place under the name Plant Power Celebration. The first one was held on 30 October 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/saigonveganfestival/|title=Saigon Vegan Festival|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Europe ==\n{{see also|Veganmania|VeggieWorld}}\n\n=== Belgium ===\nVegan Summer Fest is organized by BE Vegan.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegan Summer Fest|url=http://bevegan.be/vegan-summer-fest/|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Czechia ===\n[[Fluff Fest]] is an independent [[hardcore punk]] festival held each July in [[Rokycany]]. It is fully vegan, with catering provided by local animal rights organization Svoboda zv\u00ed\u0159at.<ref name=\"idioteq2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.idioteq.com/a-look-inside-fluff-fest-exclusive-interview/|title=A Look Inside Fluff Fest!|first=Karol|last=Kami\u0144ski|publisher=Idioteq|date=28 January 2013|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Greece ===\nThe Vegan Life Festival (veganlife.gr) is a celebration in several Greek cities that presents vegan lifestyles, products, and practices through speeches, workshops, brochures, stalls with companies that provide vegan products, activities for children, and vegan food and sweets.  Admission open to the general public is free.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athensculturenet.com/en/event/vegan-life-festival-athens-2018|title=The Vegan Life Festival. Athens Culture Net. Accessed 12/26/2018|author=|date=|website=athensculturenet.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.veganlife.gr/|title=Veganlife|author=|date=|website=Veganlife|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  YouTube video documentation is available.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCWEP-c1VWkxt5Hcd6WQFSJw|title=Vegan Life Festival|author=|date=|website=YouTube|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Athens ====\nThe Vegan Life Festival has been held in several cities in Greece since November 5, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/%CF%84%CE%B5%CF%87%CE%BD%CF%8C%CF%80%CE%BF%CE%BB%CE%B9%CF%82-%CE%B4%CE%AE%CE%BC%CE%BF%CF%85-%CE%B1%CE%B8%CE%B7%CE%BD%CE%B1%CE%AF%CF%89%CE%BD/vegan-life-festival-2016/178401362613208/|title=Vegan Life Festival 2016|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> The 2017 Vegan Life Festival was held in Athens on July 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.veganeventhub.com/event/vegan-life-festival-athens-2017/|title=Vegan Life Festival Athens 2017|author=|date=6 June 2017|website=veganeventhub.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> Buildout plans for nine Greek cities are being implemented gradually.  Organizers claim an attendance of greater than 18,000 visitors{{citation needed|date=December 2018}} at the 2018 Athens event, held at the Technopolis of the Municipality.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaboutfestivals.gr/en/festivals/vegan-life-festival-2/|title=Vegan Life Festival 2018|author=|date=|website=allaboutfestivals.gr|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/veganlifefestival/vegan-life-festival-athens-2018/2058390741104185/|title=Vegan Life Festival Athens 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/veganlifefestival/events|title=Vegan Life Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegevents.com/events/vegan-life-festival/|title=Vegan Life Festival|author=|date=|website=Veg Events|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>[https://www.happycow.net/reviews/vegan-life-festival-athens-142276 Vegan Life Festival/  HappyCow.net.  Accessed 12/26/2018]</ref>\n\n==== Thessaloniki ====\nVegan Life Festival since 2017.  The 2018 was held May 20. 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://livingcrueltyfree.gr/en/vegan-life-festival-thessaloniki-2018/|title=VEGAN LIFE FESTIVAL THESSALONIKI 2018!|last=Zoe|date=11 May 2018|website=livingcrueltyfree.gr|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== Chania ====\nThe Vegan Life Festival is scheduled to begin in Chania in 2019.\n\n==== Malta ====\nFrom August 5\u20136, 2018, the Vegan Life Festival was held at The Floriana Granaries in Malta.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://veganguidegreece.com/vegan-life-festival/|title=Vegan Life Festival \u2013 Vegan Guide Greece|author=|date=|website=veganguidegreece.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Ireland ===\nDublin Vegfest is the Irish capital's vegan festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dublinvegfest.com/|title=22nd & 23rd September 2018 \u2013 Dublin Vegfest|website=dublinvegfest.com}}</ref>\n\n=== Italy ===\nVeganFest Bologna is a vegan event in Europe which had more than 43,000 visitors in 2014. The event took place in [[Bologna]] in September 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=VeganFest Bologna|url=http://www.veganfest.it/?page_id=5188|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\nFestival The Vegetarian Chance (www.thevegetarianchance.org) was founded in 2014 by journalist Gabriel Eschenazi and chef Pietro Leemann. First Festival in the world which includes a haute cuisine vegan contest with international chefs. Out of the contest the program includes show cookings, lectures, movies and a small market. Five editions were held in Milan and the last one in Turin (11-13 October). Next edition will be held on 24-25-26 October in Milan.\n\n=== Hungary ===\n\n==== Budapest ====\nThe XIX Vegetarian Festival was organized in August 2015 in [[Budapest]]. {{citation needed|date=October 2015}}\n\n=== Netherlands ===\n[[File:Psyfi.jpg|thumb|[[Psy-Fi]] in Leeuwarden, Netherlands]]\n* [[VeggieWorld]] in [[Utrecht]], since 2016, vegan<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://nos.nl/op3/artikel/2090859-gaat-het-nieuwe-vlees-het-oude-vlees-verslaan.html |title=Gaat het nieuwe vlees het oude vlees verslaan? |work=NOS |date=5 March 2016 |accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Nederlandse Vereniging voor Veganisme|VegFest]] in Utrecht, since 2014, vegan<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.trouw.nl/home/naakte-demonstranten-op-de-bres-voor-veganisme~afe5eb72/ |title=Naakte demonstranten op de bres voor veganisme |author=Amber Dujardin |work=Trouw |date=1 November 2014 |accessdate=25 March 2017}}</ref>\n* Veggie Fair in [[Lisserbroek]], since 2013, vegetarian<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.veganisme.org/event/veggiefair/ |title=VeggieFair 2016 |publisher=Nederlandse Vereniging voor Veganisme |accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe following music festivals have made a conscious decision not to sell any meat on the festival terrain: Digital Festival (DGTL) in [[Amsterdam]] (since 2016),<ref name=\"verbaasd\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.rtlnieuws.nl/nieuws/nederland/artikel/4208246/festival-milkshake-verbaasd-over-heftige-reacties-op-vegetarisch |title=Festival Milkshake verbaasd over heftige reacties op vegetarisch eten |work=RTL Nieuws |date=27 May 2018 |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"UITgezocht\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nu.nl/uit/5291708/uitgezocht-worden-festivals-vleesvrij.html |title=UITgezocht: Worden festivals vleesvrij? |work=NU.nl |date=31 May 2018 |accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> Lente Kabinet in [[Oostzaan]] (since 2018),<ref name=\"UITgezocht\"/> Festival Milkshake in Amsterdam (since 2018),<ref name=\"verbaasd\"/><ref name=\"UITgezocht\"/> and [[Psy-Fi]] in [[Leeuwarden]] (starting from 2019).<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.lc.nl/friesland/article24264539.ece |title=Psy-Fi verduurzaamt verder: volgende editie volledig vegetarisch |author=Yme Gietema |work=Leeuwarder Courant |date=13 March 2019 |accessdate=28 March 2019 |language=nl}}</ref> Organisers indicated their motives were sustainability and environmental protection; aside from dropping meat sales, they also focused on reducing the use of [[disposable product]]s and electricity.<ref name=\"verbaasd\"/><ref name=\"UITgezocht\"/>\n\n=== Spain ===\n\n==== Alicante ====\nVegan Fest [[Alicante]] has been organized by Alacant Rock since 2014. It is the only vegan festival in [[Spain]]. {{citation needed|date=October 2015}}\n\n=== Portugal ===\n\n==== Lisbon ====\nVegan\u00e1rio Fest [[Lisbon]] (www.veganario.org) has been organized since 2008 by a group of friends in punk/hardcore community with help of local HareKrishna Community. It is the oldest of its kind in Lisbon and has been growing in the last years. \nIt gathers a lot of organizations and small businesses and important people in the vegan community to talk about and spread veganism.\n\nThe music slowed down, it is more open to all the people. It is growing: Approximately 300/600px until 2014, more than 1500 in 2015, over 2000 in 2016, and more than 3500 in 2017.\n\n=== United Kingdom ===\n==== ''England'' ==== \n===== Birmingham =====\nBirmingham Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\">[https://www.viva.org.uk/festivals/contact#contact Contact form for VIVA's Vegan Festivals, which supplement previously existing vegan festivals in UK]</ref>\n\n===== Bournemouth =====\nApproximately 90 stalls, talks, and food.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170511025420/http://www.dorsetveganevents.co.uk/bournemouthveganfair.html|title=Bournemouth Vegan Fair \u2013 17 & 18 June 2017 \u2013 Dorset Vegan Events|author=|date=11 May 2017|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Bradford =====\nBradford Vegan Festival was held on Sunday 2 September 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/category/Community/veganfestivaluk/posts/|title=Bradford Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and again will be held in September 2019.\n\n===== Brighton =====\nBrighton Vegan Festival took place on Saturday 14 July 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/brightonveganfestival2018/|title=Brighton Vegan & Ethical Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> and again will occur in July 2019.\n\nBrighton Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Bristol, Brighton, London =====\n{{see also|Vegfest (UK)}}\nVegfestUK Bristol was held May 26\u201327 at Ashton Gate stadium, Ashton Road, BS3 2EJ Bristol, United Kingdom.  Standard advance day tickets are \u00a311.00 (adults), \u00a36.00 (concessions) [including booking fees] and \u00a35.50 (children)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/ashton-gate-stadium/vegfestuk-bristol-2018/713055975565881/|title=VegfestUK Bristol 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://accounts.google.com/ServiceLogin?passive=1209600&osid=1&continue=https://plus.google.com/communities/111382870961138557305&followup=https://plus.google.com/communities/111382870961138557305|title=Sign in \u2013 Google Accounts|website=accounts.google.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> but was actually held from October 27\u201328, 2018, at Olympia London. The announcement was made in September 2018, citing higher than expected costs and broad availability of good quality vegan food in Bristol, that VegFestUK organizers would not schedule another event in Bristol for 2019 or 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/ashton-gate-stadium/vegfestuk-bristol-2018/713055975565881/|title=VegfestUK Bristol 2018|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/vegfestexpress/2018/09/statement-on-the-future-of-vegfestuk-bristol|title=Statement on the future of VegfestUK Bristol|website=Statement on the future of VegfestUK Bristol|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> but that VegFestUK would continue to hold annual events elsewhere.\n\n===== Coventry =====\nCoventry Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Liverpool =====\nLiverpool Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== London =====\nJustVShow is held in July<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.justvshow.co.uk|title=Just V Show \u2013 Vegan & Vegetarian Show in London & Glasgow|website=Just V Show}}</ref> and [[Vegfest (UK)|Vegfest]] (14,500 visitors in 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vegfest.co.uk/our-events/|title=Our events|website=VegfestUK|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>) is held in autumn. Plant Powered Expo takes place for the first time in February 2020, just after [[Veganuary]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.plantpoweredexpo.co.uk/|title=Home|website=Plant Powered Expo|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n\nLondon Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Kent =====\nMaidstone Vegan Festival took place for the second time on July 29, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maidstoneveganfestival.co.uk/|title=Maidstone Vegan Festival|website=Maidstoneveganfestival.co.uk|language=English|access-date=2017-03-19}}</ref>\n\n===== Newcastle =====\nNewcastle Vegan Festival took place on Sunday 1 July 2018 from 10:30 AM \u2013 4:30 PM UTC+01 in Newcastle upon Tyne.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/newcastleveganfest|title=Newcastle Vegan Festival|website=https://www.facebook.com/newcastleveganfest|language=English|access-date=2018-04-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/Causes/newcastle-vegan-festival-2018-vegan-awards/1645580835499105/|title=Newcastle VEGAN Festival 2018 + Vegan Awards|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Nottingham =====\nNottingham Viva! Vegan Festival<ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Sheffield =====\nSheffield Vegan Festival will be held on Saturday 15 September 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/sheffieldveganfestival/|title=Sheffield Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== ''Scotland'' ====\n===== Aberdeen =====\nAberdeen Vegan Festival took place on Sunday 8 July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/aberdeenveganfest/|title=Aberdeen Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Cardiff =====\nCardiff Vegan Festival occurred on Saturday 22 September 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/cardiffveganfestival/|title=Log In or Sign Up to View|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"viva.org.uk\"/>\n\n===== Edinburgh =====\nEdinburgh Vegan Festival took place on Sunday 19 August 2018 in Murrayfield Stadium.  This is the first annual Edinburgh Vegan Festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/edinburghveganfest/|title=Edinburgh Vegan Festival|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://veganfestival.co.uk/edinburgh-schools-vegan/|title=Edinburgh Schools Have Gone Plant Based|author=|date=25 April 2018|website=veganfestival.co.uk|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Glasgow =====\nJustVShow is held in July.<ref name=\"auto\"/>  The Glasgow JustVShow is scheduled for July 2\u20133, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.justvshow.co.uk/scotland/|title=Just V Show \u2013 Vegan & Vegetarian Show in Glasgow|website=Glasgow, Scotland, Just V Show}}</ref>  In 2018 the JustVShow is co-locating with The Allergy & Free From Show Scotland 2018.\n\n== North America ==\n\n=== Canada ===\n====Alberta====\n=====Edmonton=====\nThe first Edmonton VegFest was held from 10 am to 6 pm on September 30, 2018, at the Ritchie Community League Hall and Outdoor Park, \n7727 98th Street Northwest, Edmonton, Alberta T6E 5C9. Admission was free. The nonprofit organization coordinating and hosting this annual event was Vegans and Vegetarians of Alberta.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edmontonjournal.com/life/food/new-vegetable-festival-launches-in-ritchie-with-fun-shopping-and-greens|title=New Edmonton vegetable festival in Ritchie offers shopping, greens \u2013 Edmonton Journal|first1=Liane|last1=Faulder|date=20 September 2018|website=edmontonjournal.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.todocanada.ca/vegfest-edmonton/|title=VegFest Edmonton \u2013 Ritchie Community League Hall & Park, 7727 98 Street Northwest, Edmonton|author=|date=|website=To Do Canada|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.infoedmonton.com/event/vegfest/|title=VegFest|date=22 August 2019|website=InfoEdmonton|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/vegfest-edmonton-2018/182759825765331/|title=VegFest Edmonton 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/vvoaclub/|title=Vegans and Vegetarians of Alberta|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Ontario====\n=====Guelph=====\nVegfest Guelph<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegfestguelph.ca|title=Vegfest Guelph|website=Vegfest Guelph}}</ref> is an annual festival. The 2016 festival took place on Sunday, September 25, 2016, at Goldie Mill and the Guelph Youth Music Centre.\n\n=====Toronto=====\nThe Vegetarian Food Festival in Toronto attracted over 50,000 attendees in 2014 and featured more than 120 food and product vendors.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegetarian Food Festival Toronto|url=http://veg.ca/festival|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> It is a free public festival held at Harbourfront Centre by the [[Toronto Vegetarian Association]] in Toronto the second weekend of every September.  It was first held in 1985 and is believed to be the largest and longest continuously running vegetarian food festival in North America, and is credited with having inspired the broad vegetarian food festival movement in the United States, which was first copied by the long-running [[Boston Vegetarian Society|Boston Vegetarian Food Festival]].\n\nThe Toronto Vegan Food and Drink Festival, a fully vegan food and drink festival in the city, strives to present an all vegan experience featuring comfort food, craft brews, wine and spirits.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vegan Food and Drink Festival Toronto|url=https://www.vegandrinkfest.com/toronto/}}</ref>\n\nThe Toronto Vegan Expo (formerly known as Vegan Spring Expo) was a free annual vegan festival that took place in Toronto from 2011 to 2013 and had an attendee record of 1500 in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.veganspringexpo.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141222123329/http://www.veganspringexpo.com/|url-status=dead|title=502 Bad Gateway nginx openresty 185.15.56.1|archivedate=22 December 2014|accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Niagara (St. Catharines)=====\nNiagara VegFest began in 2012 and is an annual event that takes place in downtown St. Catharines, Ontario.<ref>{{cite web|title=Niagara VegFest|url=http://niagaravegfest.com|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref> The 2012 Niagara VegFest closed with a screening of [[Vegucated]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.getvegucated.com/ |title=Vegucated |publisher=Getvegucated.com |date= |accessdate=2012-09-17}}</ref>\n\n=====Ottawa=====\nThe first Ottawa Veg Fest was held in 2009, and was organized by the National Capital Vegetarian Association.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ottawa Veg Fest|url=http://vegfest.ca|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n=====Kingston=====\nThe first Kingston Veg Fest was held in the fall of 2016. It is being organized by the Kingston Vegetarian Network<ref>{{cite web|title=Kingston Vegetarian Network|url=http://kingstonveg.ca |accessdate=14 December 2015}}</ref>\n\n=====Mississauga=====\nThe first Mississauga Veg Fest was held in May 2018. Mississauga Veg Fest was the city's first vegan festival! Over 60 vendors were in attendance to showcase the GTHA's finest veg-based food, drink, clothing & accessories, products, advocate groups and children's activities. It is being organized by a private volunteer committee<ref>{{cite web|title=Mississauga Veg Fest|url=https://mississaugavegfest.ca |accessdate=21 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n=====Muskoka=====\nMuskoka VegFest had its inaugural event on Aug 11, 2018. 68 Vendors and various speakers drew in a crowd of just under 5000 people.  The annual event is run by a private volunteer committee.  It is a not-for profit event.<ref>{{cite web|title=Muskoka Veg Fest|url=http://muskokavegfest.com|accessdate=8 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Quebec====\n=====Montreal=====\nThe first Montreal Vegan Festival was held from September 26\u201327, 2014 and welcomed over 5,000 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://festivalveganedemontreal.com/2014en/|title=2014\u2013 Montreal Vegan Festival \u2013 September 26\u201327, 2014|website=2014\u2013 Montreal Vegan Festival}}</ref>\n\n====M\u00e9xico====\n\n=====Baja California=====\n\nTijuana Veggie Fest 2018 was held on July 6, 2018, in Centro Cultural Tijuana (CECUT), Paseo de los H\u00e9roes No. 9350, Zona Urbana R\u00edo, Tijuana, Baja California.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/tjveggiefest/tijuana-veggie-fest-2018/148377289195497/|title=Tijuana Veggie Fest 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Tijuana Veggie Fest 2019 is tentatively scheduled for June 29, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/VeggieFestTijuana/|title=Tijuana Veggie Fest 2019 Facebook page. Accessed December 26, 2018|author=|date=|website=facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Jalisco=====\nVegan Fest M\u00e9xico was held from November 12\u201313, Jalisco in 2016, at Parque Agroecologico Zapopan, Zapopan, Jalisco, Mexico, and is scheduled again for future years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/VeganFestMexico/|title=Vegan Fest M\u00e9xico|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/SaborVegano/vegan-fest-jalisco/192341267867263/|title=Vegan Fest Jalisco|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  \"Primer Festival Vegano en la ZMG de Guadalajara organizado por activistas del movimiento de Derechos Animales.\"\n\n=== United States ===\nOver 120 VegFests are scheduled for the United States<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americanvegan.org/vegfests.htm|title=American Vegan Society's list of 2018 VegFests in the United States, accessed July 17, 2018|author=|date=|website=americanvegan.org|accessdate=22 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190210223053/http://www.americanvegan.org/vegfests.htm|archive-date=10 February 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> in 33 states plus Puerto Rico.  The oldest continuously-held vegetarian food festival seems to be that in Boston (May 1996), organized by the [[Boston Vegetarian Society]] and originally copied from the event which the Toronto Vegetarian Society has been managing since 1985.  Some of the American VegFests<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegevents.com/festivals/|title=Upcoming Plant-Based and Vegan Festivals|author=|date=|website=Veg Events|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> are: Veggie Fest Every second Saturday in January, [[Killeen, Texas]].\n\n==== Arizona ====\n===== Phoenix =====\nThe Phoenix (PHX) Vegan Food and Beer Fest was held on February 24, 2018. in Margaret T. Hance Park, 1202 N. 3rd Street, in Phoenix, AZ.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://phxveganfest.com/|title=Phoenix Vegan Festival \u2013 Farm fresh for 2018|website=phxveganfest.com}}</ref>\n\nThe Arizona Vegan Fest is scheduled for 22\u201323 December 2018, in Centennial Plaza, 9875 N 85th Ave, Peoria, AZ 85345. The organizers produce 2\u20133 free vegan festivals each year for Arizonans. AZ Vegan Fest seeks to concentrate Arizona's high quality vegan cuisine, products, ideas, and entertainment each year!<ref>{{cite web|url=http://azveganfest.com/|title=AZ Vegan Fest | website=azveganfest.com}}</ref>\n\n===== Scottsdale =====\nThe Arizona Veg Food Fest was held January 20\u201321, 2018, in the Scottsdale Civic Center Amphitheater in [[Scottsdale, Arizona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018215349/http://azvegfoodfest.com/|title=New York Veg Food Fest|author=|date=18 October 2014|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\nUnder different auspices and with slightly different organizing principles, a Scottsdale VegOut Vegan Festival was also held March 17\u201318, 2018.\n\n===== Sedona =====\nThe Sedona Vegfest was held January 20\u201321, 2018, in the Sedona Performing Arts Center.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://healthyworldsedona.com/sedona-vegfest-2017/|title=Sedona VegFest Celebration of Plant-Based Nutrition|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===== Tucson =====\nThe Third Annual VegFest Tucson is scheduled for Sunday, November 11, 2018, from 10am-5pmm at The Whistle Stop Depot, 127 W. 5th Street, in [[Tucson, Arizona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://foodinroot.com/veg/|title=Veg|website=FoodInRoot|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>  It is organized by It is organized by VegOut Tucson.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vegoutevents.com/tucson-2018|title=2018 TUCSON \u2013 Vegout Events|author=|date=|website=VegOut! Events|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== California ====\n===== Berkeley =====\nThe annual Berkeley Vegan Earth Day is organized by Compassionate Living and longtime activist Hope Bohanec and was held on Sunday, April 22, 2018 \u2013 [[Earth Day]] \u2013 at the [[David Brower Center]] in [[Berkeley, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berkeleyveganearthday.com/|title=Berkeley Earth Day|website=Berkeleyveganearthday.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Encino =====\nVegFest L.A. (formerly WorldFest, a very popular event) was held on May 6, 2018, at 6004\u20136076 Woodley Avenue in [[Encino, California]], a neighborhood in the [[San Fernando Valley]] region of [[Los Angeles]].  \"World Fest was a solar-powered, day-long event filled with music, food, film and celebrities to raise public awareness of the veggie lifestyle. The first WorldFest was in 2000 at the same site, and was modeled after the San Diego FallFest held in 1999 in Ocean Beach.  This conference operated annually for thirteen years as WorldFest before being rebranded as VegFest.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfestevents.com/|title=World Fest \u2013 Music, Food, Film for the Veggie Lifestyle|website=Worldfestevents.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Irvine =====\nThe annual Vegan PlantFest was held on February 24, 2018, at Tanaka Farms in Irvine, California.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tanakafarms.com/events/2018/2/24/vegan-plant-fest-1000-to-300-no-reservation-needed|title=VEGAN PLANT FEST: 10:00 to 3:00 \u2013 no reservation needed|author=|date=|website=Tanaka Farms|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== Long Beach =====\nThe second annual Long Beach Vegan Food & Music Festival was scheduled for July 8, 2017, and the third annual event is being scheduled for mid-July 2018, from 11 am to 7 pm, at Rainbow Lagoon Park, 400 Shoreline Village Drive, in [[Long Beach, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lbveganfest.com/home.html|title=Home|author=|date=|website=Long Beach Vegan Food and Music Festival|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  Co-organizers Edward Yniguez and his wife, Kawani Brown, produce it annually.  Because the first year's event was free, reportedly between 8,500 and 10,000 people showed up throughout the day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lbpost.com/life/food/lbvf-recap/|title=Long Beach Vegan Fest Draws an Estimated 10,000 Attendees to Rainbow Lagoon Park \u2022 Long Beach Post|author=|date=|website=lbpost.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  But 2017 tickets cost $17 (general admission) to $45 (VIP tickets) each.\n\n===== Los Angeles =====\nThe Vegan Street Fair Los Angeles was held on March 25, 2018, at 11223 Chandler Boulevard in North Hollywood, California.\n\nThe Seed Food and Wine LA & Food Festival was held from May 23\u201327, 2018, in [[Los Angeles]], but some scheduling uncertainties remain.\n\nCalifornia Vegetarian Food Festival 2018 is scheduled for September 29, 2018, at Raleigh Studios Hollywood, 5300 Melrose Avenue, [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cavegfoodfest.com/|title=Home|author=|date=|website=www.cavegfoodfest.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref> U.S. Veg Corp, organizer of this festival, is also organizing the NYC Vegetarian Food Festival 2018, to be held Saturday, May 19, 2018, beginning at 11:00 AM, at Metropolitan Pavilion, [[New York City]], where tickets are $30 \u2013 $75 each.\n\n===== Oakland =====\nOaklandVeg organizes an annual VegWeek in mid-May in [[Oakland, California]].  The 2018 event was held from May 12\u201320, ending with the Oakland VegFest, which was held for May 20, 2018, from 11 am to 5 pm, at the Lake Merritt Amphitheater.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150219143242/http://oaklandveg.com/overview/|title=Overview \u2013 Oakland Veg \u2013 California|author=|date=19 February 2015|website=web.archive.org|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://oaklandvegfest.com/|title=Oakland VegFest|website=oaklandvegfest.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/1896232510620160/|title=2017 Oakland VegFest|website=Facebook.com|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===== Pasadena =====\nThe Eat Drink Vegan (Formerly Known as Vegan Beer & Food Festival) was held on May 26, 2018, on [[Memorial Day]] Weekend, in [[Rose Bowl (stadium)|The Rose Bowl]] in [[Pasadena]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eatdrinkvegan.com/|title=Eat Drink Vegan|author=|date=|website=Eat Drink Vegan|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  The Festival features unlimited pours of the region's best craft beer, wine, ciders, kombucha, cold brew, craft sodas, and tea tastings at the Rose Bowl and Brookside Golf Course... and involves 100+ exhibitors who are restaurants, food carts, trucks, and other vendors. The Green Saturday Vegan Marketplace showcases vendors selling products from clothing to skin care.\n\n===== Sacramento =====\nThe SacTown VegFest, was held January 27, 2018, in the Sacramento High School, 2315 34th Street.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sactownvegfest.org/|title=SacTown VegFest|website=SacTown VegFest}}</ref>  The 2019 event will be scheduled for a comparable date.\n\n===== San Diego =====\nThe Vegan Street Fair San Diego Nights was held Saturday, May 12, 2018, at Anthem Vegan in San Diego.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kpbs.org/events/2018/may/12/vegan-street-fair-san-diego/?et=91182|title=Vegan Street Fair San Diego|author=|date=|website=KPBS Public Media|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>  For hygienic and permit reasons, dogs were not allowed at the food event.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/events/vegan-street-fair-vegas-nights-2018/171428313499043/|title=Vegan Street Fair Vegas Nights 2018|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com|accessdate=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===== San Jose =====\nThe South Bay VegFair is scheduled for June 16, 2018, at the Santa Clara County Fairgrounds in [[San Jose, California]].<ref>https://www.summerveg.com/</ref>\n